      "text": "✈️ This is what it looks like at 3:30 am Sunday at Austin’s airport. Travelers are being encouraged to get here 2.5 hours before domestic flights, 3 for international.\n\nMeanwhile, President Trump is thanking TSA agents for going to work but \"not being paid\" amid an ongoing partial government shutdown, which has seen agents quitting and absences doubling. \n\nHe blamed the “radical left” in a social media post Saturday for refusing \"to honor the deal that was approved and voted on in Congress.\" He directed portions of the post to TSA agents and said, \"Keep fighting for the USA. GO TO WORK! I promise that I will never forget you!!!",
